1. A company has a VPC that has a private IP address space of 10.0.0.0/16. The company has used up all the existing private IP space. A SysOps administrator must resolve this issue with a solution that minimizes complexity and maximizes cost-effectiveness.

Which solution meets these requirements?

2. Question
A telecommunications company is developing a new application. A third-party vendor is passing observability log files through Amazon EventBridge to invoke an AWS Lambda function. The Lambda function processes the log files and then writes the results to an Amazon S3 bucket. In testing, EventBridge is sending all log files immediately to an Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) dead-letter queue instead of attempting any retry.

Which step should the SysOps administrator take to troubleshoot this issue?


3. Question
A company hosts an internal application on Amazon EC2 instances. All application data and requests route through an AWS Site-to-Site VPN connection between the on-premises network and AWS. The company must monitor the application for changes that allow network access outside of the corporate network. Any change that exposes the application externally must be restricted automatically. 

Which solution meets these requirements in the MOST operationally efficient manner?

4. Question
